 A 26-year-old woman allegedly stabbed a 24-year-old man to
death. According to police spokesperson Captain Sergio Kock it’s
alleged that on Tuesday night, the woman entered the ex-boyfriend’s place in
Phelindaba, Barkly West. “She found the man with his new girlfriend,” Kock said. Kock said the ex-boyfriend opened the door and the female
allegedly stabbed him in his upper leg with a knife. “The man tried to
seek help but collapsed just outside his place and succumbed to his injuries,” Kock
said. The police arrested the female minutes later at her house,
not far from the scene. The suspect is expected to be appearing in the Barkly West
Magistrates’ Court soon. Police are  investigation the murder further.